cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB 

This paper deals with ontology matching and semantic search, which are topics related to natural language processing and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the use of algorithms and metrics for semantic distance calculations suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) could also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the development of a parser software for Wiktionary indicates that cs.DB (Databases) could be a possible sub-category as well.
